 Code Style Guidelines
Use single quotes for strings
Use 2 spaces for indentation
Maximum line length of 100 characters
Always use semicolons
Use camelCase for variables, functions, and method names
Use PascalCase for classes, interfaces, and type names
Use UPPER_SNAKE_CASE for constants
Group imports by type (standard library, third-party, local)
Prefer arrow functions for anonymous functions
Avoid files longer than 300 lines (refactor if necessary)
Always add access modifiers (public, private, protected) to class members
Use async/await instead of raw promises
Add meaningful comments for complex logic
Write descriptive variable and function names